body_html:
I faced the same issue too but managed to fix it by generating the .pb file using TensorFlow 1.1.* (according to answers in StackOverflow).

As I understand it, the protobuf framework version in our desktop generating the .pb file must be of the same version as the one residing in iOS after Pod installation.

https://www.tensorflow.org/mobile/linking_libs#protobuf_problems

... [T]his generated code needs to be linked against shared libraries for the exact same version of the framework that was used for the generator.

body:
I faced the same issue too but managed to fix it by generating the `.pb` file using TensorFlow 1.1.* (according to answers in StackOverflow).

As I understand it, the protobuf framework version in our desktop generating the `.pb` file must be of the same version as the one residing in iOS after Pod installation.

https://www.tensorflow.org/mobile/linking_libs#protobuf_problems
> ... [T]his generated code needs to be linked against shared libraries for the **exact same version** of the framework that was used for the generator.
